description:
&lt;p&gt;#teamAcute are seeking dynamic Housekeeper with a passion for acute care&lt;br /&gt;Lancashire Teaching Hospitals Trust is one of the biggest and highest performing Trusts in the North West. The Trust operates from two sites the Chorley District Hospital and the Royal Preston Hospital. The Royal Preston Hospital is the Major Trauma Centre for the Lancashire and South Cumbria Major Trauma Network and have tertiary services which include neurosurgery, vascular and stroke.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;MAU is a fast passed high turnover unit we see over 700 new admissions per month and we take admissions direct from the Emergency department and same day emergency care unit. We care for patients within their acute phase and this can vary from elderly care to critically unwell patents, patients with long term conditions and mental health issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is integral to ensuring the unit is able to function efficiently on a daily basis .The role holder will be proactive ,driven and able to use initiative .You be working closely with the MAU nursing team in order to properly maintain the patient environment . The role consists of making sure the unit is tidy, supporting the team with patient’s meals and refreshments and to maintain the stock room supply levels. We need the role holder to have excellent people skills be enthusiastic with a positive can do attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you think that this is for you please apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
